title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message:
Hi,

I have an A1466 820-3209-A that has green light, but no fan spin.

It takes 0.400 A no PSU and them drops to around 0.250A.

I think that I have a short on PPCPUVCCIO_S0_REG because on L7630 I get:

Diode mode =0.0216V and 11.90 ohm off resistance to ground.

Is this shorted or low resistance circuit?

Can you help?

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message:
I don't think to be low value, for this PCH.
Which voltages do you get on the coils?

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message:
ISL95870 fails a lot.
Post U7600 voltages; pins 3, 13, 14.
If good, change U7600.

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message:
U7600 :

3 = 0.5V
13 = 5.1V
14 = 5.1

CPUVCCIOS0_EN seams low, isen't it?

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message: Just replaced U7600 but still the same. No fan spin, and the same values on pins. 3. 13 and 14 of U7600

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message:
Check R/C7981.

Do NOT change components w/o real reason in the future.

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message:
Hi, sorry. I was not sure and decided to replace it.
R/C7981 are good, and on PIN 3 of U7780 I also get 0.5V

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message:
"Check R/C7981
------
R/C7981 are good"
At least one is bad.
Replace them, don't check with "eyes only".

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message: R7981 has 20K ohm, and 3.3V on both pins, and C7981 isen't shorted (diode mode has normal values). I'll replace both just for sure.

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message:
Don't replace then.
Check the trace to U7600.

title: A1466 820-32-09-A no power
message:
You're right. It was the trace to U7600...
Thank you!
